headline: Wall Street Hates the Idea of a ‘Shadow’ Fed Chair. It May Already Have One
summary: The Federal Reserve may already have the so-called shadow chairman that President Donald Trump has said he might soon appoint in a move that could be seen as part of a pressure campaign to lower interest rates and reduce government borrowing costs.  Trump has been relentless with his criticism of Fed Chairman Jerome Powell, and raised expectations that he would fire him earlier this week, before changing course as markets reacted.  Powell hasn’t given in, as inflation remains stubbornly north of the central bank’s 2% target and labor market data continues to show near-full employment.

headline: US Financial 15 Split Corp. Preferred Dividend Declared
summary: TORONTO, July 18, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- US Financial 15 Split Corp ("US Financial 15") declares its monthly distribution of $0.06533 for each Preferred share, or 10.00% annually based on the previous month end net asset value. Distributions are payable August 8, 2025 to shareholders on record as at July 31, 2025. US Financial 15 invests in a portfolio consisting of 15 U.S. financial services companies as follows: American Express, Bank of America, Bank of New York Mellon Corp., Citigroup, CME
